TITLE: Airlines Cap Fares as Southwest Cancellations Continue
SUMMARY: Carriers including American, Delta and United are implementing fare caps in some cities following an influx of last-minute bookings after Southwest scrapped thousands of flights.

TITLE: EU Foreign-Subsidy Limits Target China but Also Hit U.S.
SUMMARY: Under rules taking effect next year, the Inflation Reduction Act and other aid could trigger hefty reporting requirements.

TITLE: Inflation Takes Biggest Bite From Middle-Income Households
SUMMARY: Purchasing power from paychecks fell for middle-income households in 2022, while rising for those at the bottom and top.

TITLE: Google Maps Chief Sees New Directions for Digital Navigation
SUMMARY: A more immersive experience is coming to map tools, says Google Geo head Christopher Phillips

TITLE: Amazon Unionization Stalls Amid Turnover, Firm's Efforts
SUMMARY: Organizing is set to continue at Amazon and other companies but may proceed more slowly and take years to play out, labor researchers say.

TITLE: Why So Many Accountants Are Quitting
SUMMARY: Wooing students to the field is tough. Even some accounting majors don’t want accounting jobs.

TITLE: With New EVs Arriving, Brand Loyalty Goes Out the Window
SUMMARY: As more car makers roll out electric vehicles, they are discovering that early customers are far more apt to try new brands.

TITLE: Baby-Formula Imports to Face Tariffs Again in 2023
SUMMARY: Temporary exemptions put in place during a U.S. shortage will expire soon, as supply improves.

TITLE: U.S. Accounting Rule Maker Looks to Advance Projects on Tax, Crypto and Expenses in 2023
SUMMARY: The Financial Accounting Standards Board in 2023 wants to get closer to finalizing key rules, ranging from companies sharing more details on cryptocurrency holdings to breaking out certain expenses on income statements. The upshot: A wave of more work for businesses, more details for investors and more accurate accounting.

TITLE: Laid Off Tech Workers Quickly Find New Jobs
SUMMARY: Most laid off workers in tech are finding jobs shortly after beginning their search, as employers continue to scoop up workers in a tight labor market.

TITLE: Home Prices Fell in October for Fourth Straight Month
SUMMARY: Higher mortgage interest rates continue to weigh on home-buying demand, bringing an end to a pandemic-driven housing boom. Home prices slid 0.5% in October.

TITLE: At Southwest in Phoenix, a Swelling Baggage Claim and No Flights Home
SUMMARY: At times and in certain places, the Phoenix airport felt almost pandemic-like on Tuesday. Other parts of the operation, however, were teeming with passengers and bags.

TITLE: China Resumes Approving Foreign Videogames
SUMMARY: Ending a halt stretching back to June 2021, China has resumed granting publishing approvals for foreign videogames.

TITLE: Crypto Customers Sell Claims at a Loss to Avoid Bankruptcy Wait
SUMMARY: Hundreds of FTX, Voyager and Celsius customers are parting with their accounts, selling for pennies on the dollar to deep-pocketed investment firms.

TITLE: AMC Chief Asks Board for Salary Freeze in 2023
SUMMARY: CEO Adam Aron also asked senior officers to forgo raises to their cash salaries in 2023, following a painful year for the movie theater chain’s share price.

TITLE: Misleading Ads Fueled Rapid Growth of Online Mental Health Companies
SUMMARY: Online advertising has drawn thousands of people to telehealth companies for treatment of ADHD, anxiety and other conditions. Some employees and patients say these marketing practices have contributed to the abuse of controlled substances.

TITLE: U.S. Bars Imports From Three Companies, Citing Possible Forced Labor
SUMMARY: Customs used a sanctions law to target three companies that the agency says use North Korean workers, who are assumed to be forced laborers unless proven otherwise.
